About the job
Fantastic role for an Android Engineer to develop and maintain our suite of mobile apps, including our flagship Mobile Internet Banking and NAB Connect Mobile apps.

Join a flagship engineering team working on one of the bank’s highest impact\u2011 customer channels.
Accelerate your growth with hands on\u2011 delivery, real technical ownership, and mentors who genuinely support your development.
Make a real impact as part of a team that places customers at the centre of every decision.

Our people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else. Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand. 

In the role of Analyst Engineer, you will join the Digital Payment Hub team who are doubling down on moving with speed deliver this service to our customers.

Each Day, You’ll Go Above And Beyond To

Partnering with BAs and UX designers to shape clear, well defined requirements and provide technical insight.
Designing and building high quality Android applications.
Contributing actively to the full software delivery lifecycle (SDLC)
Collaborating with testers to ensure apps are reliable, performant, and resilient.
Reviewing code and giving constructive feedback to uplift engineering standards.
Driving continuous improvement in development practices, team processes, and mobile design.
Showcasing the team’s work through internal presentations and supporting events like hack days, meet\u2011ups, and demos.

We’re looking for the best and brightest to deliver for our customers. You’ll need: 

Experience developing Android apps using Java and Kotlin, with a solid understanding of mobile design patterns.
Comfortable working with REST/JSON APIs, GraphQL, microservices, and common tooling (Android Studio, Git).
Familiarity with CI/CD and build pipelines (e.g., Gradle, Jenkins) and automated testing frameworks (JUnit, Mockito, UI automation, Perfecto, Applitools).
Understanding of release and configuration management, versioning, and dependency management.
Awareness of code quality and artifact management tools (e.g., SonarQube, Artifactory).

A diverse and inclusive workplace works better for everyone

We know that our people make us who we are. That's why we have built a culture of equity and respect - where everyone feels valued and appreciated for being their authentic selves. In partnership with our multiple Employee Resource Groups (ERGs) we continue to foster an inclusive environment, where all NAB colleagues’ unique backgrounds and identities are understood, respected and celebrated. We are committed to providing an environment where you can work your way.

