About the job
This role involves updating and maintaining an existing interactive VR tour using Pano2VR. The primary focus is on refining the user experience, managing VR panoramas, and enhancing interactive elements within the established project structure. The ideal candidate will work with existing Pano2VR project files, ensuring seamless integration of new panoramas and updates to navigation and interface components. Attention to detail and a passion for interactive media are essential, as the project requires careful refinement of visual and interactive features to deliver a polished VR experience.

Deliverables

 Update and maintain Pano2VR project files for an interactive VR tour
 Import and manage new and existing 360° VR panoramas
 Refine and update interactive hotspots and navigation elements
 Adjust and maintain interface components for optimal user experience
 Publish updated versions of the VR tour for web-based deployment
 Ensure compatibility and smooth performance across supported platforms

Requirements

 Proven experience with Pano2VR and interactive panorama projects
 Strong understanding of VR workflows and visual layout in immersive environments
 Familiarity with managing and editing 360° panoramas
 Basic knowledge of HTML and JavaScript is a plus
 Detail-oriented approach with a focus on user experience and interface refinement
 Ability to work independently and efficiently within existing project structures
 Interest in interactive media and web-based VR output

About Twine

Twine is a leading freelance marketplace connecting top freelancers, consultants, and contractors with companies needing creative and tech expertise. Trusted by Fortune 500 companies and innovative startups alike, Twine enables companies to scale their teams globally.

Our Mission

Twine's mission is to empower creators and businesses to thrive in an AI-driven, freelance-first world.

