HR info was not given for "Product Testing and Systems Coordinator" with Job ID: 4391689907!

About the job
Job Description

BlueScope is an Australian-born global success story spanning 15 countries. Our team of over 16,500 people is our strength and we want our people to be safe, successful and well. We’re leaders and innovators in transforming steel into smart products and solutions that support society, today and in the future. We’re proud of brands, like COLORBOND ® steel that inspire and protect everything from hospitals to bridges and stadiums.

The Opportunity

Our Product Prototyping & Evaluation Team at the Port Kembla Manufacturing facility is looking for a Product Testing & Systems Coordinator to join their Weathering Laboratory team. As part of the broader Australian Steel Products portfolio, we have six major manufacturing sites at Port Kembla that deliver a variety of products, innovative solutions and services to our export and domestic customers.

In this role, you will play a key part in managing and improving product testing systems, laboratory processes and information systems to ensure testing activities are well governed, data integrity is maintained, and systems are fit for purpose. You’ll work closely with laboratory teams and stakeholders to support testing programs, improve processes, and enable consistent, reliable testing outcomes.

This Monday to Friday role offers market-leading superannuation, ongoing development opportunities, and participation in our annual profit\u2011share program.

What Will You Do?

Utilising your experience, knowledge, skills and critical thinking, in addition to assisting with the daily running of the Weathering Laboratory, you will improve testing systems, processes and data management across laboratory environments. You will:

coordinate, conduct and support product testing activities to enable safe, efficient and timely testing outcomes
administer and continuously identify improvements to laboratory and testing information systems to ensure accurate data capture, traceability and reporting
support the development, validation and optimisation of testing methods, procedures and systems
partner with laboratory teams and stakeholders to identify and deliver system and process improvements
analyse testing data and system outputs to drive continuous improvement, compliance and testing capability
More About You

A passion for systems, processes and product testing, and the challenge of improving how testing is planned, executed and reported, is what will make you successful. You’ll bring:

experience working with laboratory, testing or quality systems in a manufacturing or technical environment
strong capability in systems thinking, process improvement and data-driven problem solving
experience supporting or administering information systems used for testing, quality or technical data
well-developed organisational skills and the ability to manage competing priorities
a collaborative communication style, with the ability to work effectively across cross\u2011functional teams and influence stakeholders
Exposure to laboratory or testing information systems and data tools will be highly regarded. This may include experience with LIMS platforms, databases, reporting tools (e.g. Power BI), or system integration supporting testing and quality processes.

Why BlueScope

As we’re creating strength for the future through our people, products and solutions, BlueScope gives you opportunities to innovate, learn and grow with the business, supported by inclusive leadership and a positive, passionate team. At BlueScope, you’ll:

Learn and develop as you grow. With opportunities to\u202fbuild skills specific\u202fto your role and\u202faspirations,\u202four lifelong learning\u202fculture\u202fwill support your future career pathways.
Create innovative solutions. Seek better, smarter ways to solve problems, create sustainable solutions and make things happen.
Experience connection and care. Experience a positive, inclusive work environment where we look out for each other’s safety and wellbeing.
Deliver work that matters. Every action you take matters in delivering for our customers and strengthening communities for the future. We value what you do. 
At BlueScope, we offer work-life flexibility through our B-flex program. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive environment where every employee feels respected and valued to be their authentic selves, and welcome people of all backgrounds, skills, experiences and perspectives. We encourage Women and First Nations people to apply. We’re passionate about driving sustainability outcomes that matter to our communities, including action on climate and our 2050 net zero goal.

Bring your energy and make your mark, as, together, we drive Our Purpose: “We create and inspire smart solutions in steel, to strengthen communities for the future.” 

Come and discover us at www.bluescope.com/auscareers

Join us, creating strength for the future.

Applications close Monday, 13th April 2026.

